PORTFOLIO

Git Me There

Using Materialize as a front end framework, Javascript, and Walking Score and Restaurant APIs, created a website that allows users to see a location's walking score with nearby restaurants. The user can also order an Uber through the website.

Herble: A Daily Plant Guess Game

Using Tailwind CSS, Javascript for gameplay logic, AWS and Sequelize for database management, created a daily plant guessing game similar to fan favorite "Wordle". Each day, a new set of six pictures is displayed on the screen in order of decreasing guess difficulty. The user is given six chances to guess and then, depending on success, will have results appended to a leaderboard.

ABOUT

I am a full-stack web developer leveraging a background in healthcare. The skills gained from direct client care and a highly collaborative spirit make me a great asset to an innovative development team. I earned my web development certification from the University of Texas at Austin.

Well-versed in front-end languages HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Equally well-versed in back-end technologies such as SQL, MongoDB, node, Express and ORM.
